# Ticket Writing Guide

## Ticket Format (Medium/Large)

```markdown
## [EPIC-{number}] {EPIC title}

### TICKET-{number}: {ticket title}
- **User Story**: As a {role}, I want {feature}, so that {value}
- **Acceptance Criteria**:
  - [ ] Criterion 1
  - [ ] Criterion 2
  - [ ] Error handling: ...
  - [ ] Edge case: ...
- **Estimated Effort**: {0.5h ~ 2h}
- **Dependencies**: TICKET-{number} (or "None")
- **EPIC**: EPIC-{number}
```

## Small Project Ticket Format
Write a flat ticket list without EPIC grouping:

```markdown
### TICKET-{number}: {ticket title}
- **User Story**: As a {role}, I want {feature}, so that {value}
- **Acceptance Criteria**:
  - [ ] Criterion 1
  - [ ] Criterion 2
  - [ ] Error handling: ...
- **Estimated Effort**: {0.5h ~ 2h}
- **Dependencies**: TICKET-{number} (or "None")
```

## EPIC Dependencies (Medium/Large)
Always include an EPIC dependency map when writing tickets:
```markdown
## EPIC Dependency Map
EPIC-01 (Auth) → None
EPIC-02 (Dashboard) → EPIC-01
EPIC-03 (Settings) → EPIC-01, EPIC-02
```

## Rules
- Max 2 hours per ticket for a senior developer, smaller is better
- User story format is required
- Acceptance criteria must include error handling and edge cases
- Dependencies must be explicitly recorded
